WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
[Outdoor fire test area. Fire truck visible in background.]

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:12.000
[Two small wooden structures positioned side by side: left labeled "UNTREATED", right labeled "TREATED".]

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:20.000
[Text on screen: Equal amounts of kindling, wood, and lighter fluid placed inside both structures and ignited by firefighters.]

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:30.000
[Fire ignites simultaneously inside both structures.]

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:42.000
[UNTREATED structure: flames rapidly spread and engulf the entire left structure.]

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:50.000
[Screen cuts to black. Text: "SIGNAL LOST" — camera on untreated side melted from extreme heat.]

00:00:50.000 --> 00:01:02.000
[TREATED structure: fire burns initial kindling only. Flames do not spread to the wood structure itself.]

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:15.000
[UNTREATED structure continues burning with high flames. TREATED structure: fire self-extinguishes as kindling burns out.]

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:25.000
[Firefighter enters and uses hose to extinguish remaining embers in the UNTREATED structure only.]

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:35.000
[Text on screen: "M-Fire AF31 extinguishes fire completely with no firefighter intervention."]

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:40.000
[Before and after comparison displayed. M-Fire Suppression logo, website and phone number shown.]
